69th Legislature 2025 SB 37.1
1 SENATE BILL NO. 37
2 INTRODUCED BY D. EMRICH
3 BY REQUEST OF THE EDUCATION INTERIM COMMITTEE
4
5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING SCHOOL FUNDING LAWS TO CLARIFY THAT THE
6 CALCULATIONS FOR SIGNIFICANT ENROLLMENT INCREASES ARE MADE AT THE BUDGET UNIT
7 LEVEL; AMENDING SECTION 20-9-166, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE AND AN
8 APPLICABILITY DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 20-9-166, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "20-9-166. Financial support for transportation budget amendments and significant enrollment
14 increases. (1) Whenever a final budget amendment has been adopted for the transportation fund, the trustees
15 may apply to the superintendent of public instruction for an increased payment for state transportation
16 reimbursement. The superintendent of public instruction shall adopt rules for the application for state
17 transportation reimbursement. The superintendent of public instruction shall approve or disapprove each
18 application for state transportation reimbursement. When the superintendent of public instruction approves an
19 application, the superintendent of public instruction shall determine the additional amount of state transportation
20 reimbursement that will be made available to the applicant district because of additional pupil transportation
21 obligations. The superintendent of public instruction shall notify the applicant district of the superintendent's
22 approval or disapproval and, in the event of approval, the amount of additional state aid that will be made
23 available for the transportation fund. The superintendent of public instruction shall disburse the state aid to the
24 eligible district at the time the next regular state aid payment is made.
25 (2) (a) When a district experiences an enrollment increase based on the October enrollment count,
26 the district may be eligible for a significant enrollment increase payment in support of the district's general fund
27 as described in this subsection (2). All enrollment increases under this subsection (2) must be calculated
28 separately for each budget unit of a school district.
